Min: Minimum value for this axis range.
Max: Maximum value for this axis range.
GridNum: The number of grid divisions along this axis.
bSnapToGrid: If true then samples will always be snapped to the grid on this axis when added, moved, or the axes are changed.
bWrapInput: If true then the input can go outside the min/max range and the blend space is treated as being cyclic on this axis. If false then input parameters are clamped to the min/max values on this axis.
